	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">In <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=62393#62393" class="postlink">this post</a>, Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A word to all game developers:  always make cutscenes skippable.  Always always always.</div>
<br />"Always" is a strong word. <em>Super Mario Galaxy</em> for Wii uses cutscenes to cover up loading, and you can't make a "NOW LOADING" screen skippable now, can you? And how will you convince the lawyers to let the player skip the screen with copyright and trademark notices on it? And how will you handle players who are angry that they don't know where to go because they skipped the cut scene telling them the mission objective?

		

		</td>
