		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well dish you say this as if cut scenes would always be terrible. I'm not disagreeing with you at all - I just want to point that as cut scenes can be bad/boring they can as well be very fun and worth watching several times.
<br />
<br />If the scenes are not just text but also graphics with people actually moving arround, they'll usually just be a lot more fun than a bunch of text.
<br />
<br />The best example is probably Chrono Trigger, which have different scenes depending on who is in your party. I guess I beat the game 5+ times and never got bored of the scenes EVER. I think I even remembered reseting the game and trying to switch party members to get another scene.
<br />
<br />Of course whenever a scene is good or bad is subjective matter. That being said - I agree with Dish that more RPGs should have somewhere that tells you what you're supposed to no next.

		

