		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If the cutscene is 2 seconds and says "do this" that's one thing.<br /><br />If the cutscene is 5 minutes of crap you don't care about with 2 seconds of important info buried in the middle of it, that sucks.</div><br />I think you nailed it. Perhaps you can have your 2 minute cutscene, but break it up into three parts: the first minute and a half (FFing allowed), the 10 seconds that are important (no FFing unless this specific cutscene has been shown since power-on), and then the 20 second transition into gameplay (FFing allowed).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If I ask my server at a restaurant to bring me a refill of my drink and they say "do it yourself, I'm busy", that a crappy restaurant.</div><br />I take it you're not a fan of fast food with its self-service soda fountain.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If I ask a customer service guy to help me find a product and he says "that's not my job", that's a crappy store.</div><br />"That's not my department; let me get someone."<br />"Spark plugs? Aisle 13."<br />But does someone have to carry it to the checkout counter for you?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If the player asks "what am I supposed to be doing in this game now?" and the game says "tough shit, you should've watched that 5 minute cutscene at the start of the level", then that's a crappy game.</div>
<br />Then Tetrisphere is a crappy game because its rules aren't discoverable. In this game, most presses of the A button will result in damage to the player; get damaged three times in one round and your game is over. You have to find pieces that are eligible for clearing, or make them so by dragging and dropping them into place, before you line up on top of a piece and press A. But only the opening cutscene (which is skippable if it has been played at least once on that cartridge and replayable from the main menu) explains this.

		

